  input.priv    = 3;
  input.vstart = 99;  // stale QEMU1 value

  hybrid::StateDrain drain(bus);
  const auto state = drain.drain_with_passthrough(input);

  CHECK(state.vstart == 7u);  // overwritten by DM read
}
```
Tests set `input.flags |= HYBRID_FLAG_V` and populate `bus.regfile[regno_csr(...)]` with post-vsim values. The `drain_with_passthrough()` method re-reads V CSRs from the DM (via abstract commands) and overwrites stale QEMU1 values.

---

**3. Program-Buffer Tests in program_buffer.test.cpp** (verilator/tests/hybrid/program_buffer.test.cpp)

**exec_progbuf and cmderr assertion** (lines 99-119, 150-170):
```cpp
TEST_CASE("exec_progbuf: single instruction - writes insn, ebreak, exec command")
{
  RecBus bus;
  const std::array<uint32_t, 1> insns{0xDEADBEEFu};
  const bool ok = exec_progbuf(bus, insns);

  REQUIRE(ok == true);
  REQUIRE(bus.writes.size() == 3u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[0].reg == kProgbuf0);
  CHECK(bus.writes[0].val == 0xDEADBEEFu);
  CHECK(bus.writes[1].reg == kProgbuf0 + 1);
  CHECK(bus.writes[1].val == kEbreak);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].reg == 0x17u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].val == kExecProgbufCmd);
}

TEST_CASE("exec_progbuf: clears sticky cmderr before issuing exec command")
{
  RecBus bus;
  constexpr uint32_t kCmderrMask = 0x7u << 8;
  bus.read_seq[0x16u] = {kCmderrMask, 0u, 0u};

  const std::array<uint32_t, 1> insns{0x1u};
  const bool ok = exec_progbuf(bus, insns);
  REQUIRE(ok == true);

  REQUIRE(bus.writes.size() == 4u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].reg == 0x16u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].val == kCmderrMask);
  CHECK(bus.writes[3].reg == 0x17u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[3].val == kExecProgbufCmd);
}
```
The pattern: (1) call `exec_progbuf(bus, insns_span)`, (2) inspect `bus.writes` order: progbuf0..N, ebreak, optional abstractcs W1C, then kExecProgbufCmd, (3) verify `bool ok` for post-exec cmderr state. Pre-cmderr is queued in `bus.read_seq[0x16u]` so it's returned on successive reads.

---

**4. Build Registration in verilator/cmake/HybridConfig.cmake** (lines 1-125)

**How a new .test.cpp file gets compiled and registered** (lines 48-52, 81-85, 108-118):
```cmake
vsim_add_test(test_resume_driver tests/hybrid/resume_driver.test.cpp)
target_include_directories(test_resume_driver PRIVATE
  "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/../include"
)
add_dependencies(check test_resume_driver)

# ...

vsim_add_test(test_program_buffer tests/hybrid/program_buffer.test.cpp)
target_include_directories(test_program_buffer PRIVATE
  "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/../include"
)
add_dependencies(check test_program_buffer)
```
The macro `vsim_add_test(TARGET_NAME source_file.cpp)` is defined in verilator/CMakeLists.txt:538-551 and calls:
- `add_executable(TARGET_NAME EXCLUDE_FROM_ALL source_file.cpp)`
- `target_include_directories()` for VSIM_INCLUDE_DIRS, build dir, src, src/utils, and doctest external
- `target_compile_options/definitions/link_options` with standard compiler flags
- `add_test(NAME TARGET_NAME COMMAND $<TARGET_FILE:TARGET_NAME>)`
- Optional `add_dependencies(check TARGET_NAME)` to register with the `check` target

**Running a single hybrid unit test**:
```sh
cd verilator/build
ctest -R test_resume_driver -V        # run with verbose output
ctest --test-dir build -L hybrid-e2e  # run tests with label "hybrid-e2e"
```

---

**5. E2E Fixture Registration (rt_c_v_regs)** (tests/fixtures/Makefile:34, 46, 57-58, 113-115; scripts/run_e2e.sh:56, 89)

**Fixture build** (tests/fixtures/Makefile:34, 46, 113-115):
```makefile
RT_C_V_FIXTURES  := rt_c_v_regs rt_c_v_csrs rt_c_v_matmul

RT_C_V_RUNTIME_SRCS := $(RUNTIME_SRCS) $(RUNTIME_DIR)/v_regfile_xfer.c

$(RT_C_V_FIXTURES:%=%.elf): %.elf: %.c $(RT_C_V_RUNTIME_SRCS) test.ld $(RUNTIME_DIR)/rt_c_helpers.h $(RUNTIME_DIR)/v_regfile_xfer.h
	$(CC) $(RT_C_V_CFLAGS) -T test.ld \
	  $(RT_C_V_RUNTIME_SRCS) $< $(RT_C_LIBS) -o $@
```
The V fixtures compile rt_c_v_regs.c linked with crt0.S, trap.S, handler.c, and `v_regfile_xfer.c` (the Program-Buffer vector-register reload/dump sweep). The `-march=rv64gcv` flag enables RVV. The fixture depends on `v_regfile_xfer.h`.

**E2E registration and invocation** (scripts/run_e2e.sh:56, 89):
```bash
REQUIRED_ELFS=(
  ...
  rt_c_v_regs rt_c_v_csrs
  ...
)

RT_TESTS=(
  ...
  "rt_c_v_regs|FIXTURE=rt_c_v_regs"
  ...
)
```
The test name `rt_c_v_regs` maps to `FIXTURE=rt_c_v_regs` environment variable. The harness runs `tests/e2e.sh` with:
```bash
TRIGGER_MODE=csr FIXTURE=rt_c_v_regs bash tests/e2e.sh
TRIGGER_MODE=pc  FIXTURE=rt_c_v_regs bash tests/e2e.sh
```
Both modes invoke the same `tests/e2e.sh` which sources `lib/paths.sh`, resolves paths, then runs the three-phase handoff: (1) QEMU1 drains state via plugin to `$STATE_QEMU`, (2) vsim resumes and drains to `$STATE_VSIM`, (3) QEMU2 restores and continues via gdbstub.

